(233, 1, '2013-03-25 02:23:41', '2013-03-25 02:23:41', 'I started doing Web Design in High School, and co-op''d at Apogee Recording Studio in Orono, Ontario. I designed websites for my band at the time, and many other bands in the area. (My other passion was music ;)) Back in those days, I was confined to Corel Draw and an early version of Adobe Photoshop. I can''t even remember what type of text editor I was using! Memories... Anyways, after excelling in Digital Communications in High School, I enrolled in Multimedia Design &amp; Production at Fanshawe College in London, Ontario. This is where I first learned proper HTML, CSS &amp; Javascript among other things, like Graphic Design, Video Production, Flash, 3D &amp; Sound Production. I decided to focus on Web Production after in graduated in 2005, and found contracts at Ontario Children''s Mental Health, and a few other various companies doing short-term contracts.\r\n\r\nAfter moving to Toronto, my career has taken me to such agencies as Digital Cement, <a href="http://thrillworks.ca/" target="_blank">Thrillworks</a>, <a href="http://forgemedia.ca/" target="_blank">Forge Media + Design</a>, and now <a href="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/" target="_blank">The Globe and Mail</a>, where I''m currently enjoying working on their <a href="https://sec.theglobeandmail.com/subscription/?intcmp=GAMunlimited_GAMUN" target="_blank">Globe Unlimited Subscription Service</a>.', 'WEB', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'web', '', '', '2013-03-25 03:13:15', '2013-03-25 03:13:15', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=233', 0, 'page', '', 0),
