(271, 1, '2013-03-25 03:12:22', '2013-03-25 03:12:22', 'I started doing Web Design in High School, and co-op''d at Apogee Recording Studio in Orono, Ontario. I designed websites for my band at the time, and many other bands in the area. (My other passion was music ;)) Back in those days, I was confined to Corel Draw and an early version of Adobe Photoshop. I can''t even remember what type of text editor I was using! Memories... Anyways, after excelling in Digital Communications in High School, I enrolled in Multimedia Design &amp; Production at Fanshawe College in London, Ontario, which is where I first learned proper HTML, CSS &amp; Javascript among other things, like Graphic Design, Video Production, Flash, 3D &amp; Sound Production. I decided to focus on Web Production after in graduated in 2005, and found contracts at Ontario Children''s Mental Health, and a few other various companies doing short-term contracts.\r\n\r\nAfter moving to Toronto, my career has taken me to such agencies as Digital Cement, <a href="http://thrillworks.ca/" target="_blank">Thrillworks</a>, <a href="http://forgemedia.ca/" target="_blank">Forge Media + Design</a>, and now <a href="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/" target="_blank">The Globe and Mail</a>, where I''m currently enjoying working on their <a href="https://sec.theglobeandmail.com/subscription/?intcmp=GAMunlimited_GAMUN" target="_blank">Globe Unlimited Subscription Service</a>.', 'WEB', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '233-revision-4', '', '', '2013-03-25 03:12:22', '2013-03-25 03:12:22', '', 233, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=271', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(272, 1, '2013-03-25 03:25:11', '2013-03-25 03:25:11', 'I''ve loved music ever since I was a little kid growing up in the Northeast of England. Hearing my parents records growing up, and eventually moving to Canada and discovering Rock Music around the age of 9 or 10. My first real musical crush was Nirvana. They made me want to play guitar and play in a band, and I was lucky enough to get my first guitar for my eleventh birthday. Ever since then, I''ve been toiling away in basements and garages all over Southern Ontario, playing dingy little clubs and other not-so dingy clubs!\n\nMy first real band was called Torsion, which we started in 2001 and went until 2006 when we parted ways. We tried really hard to put out a record, but unfortunately didn''t work out the way we planned. Nonetheless it provided a great basis for learning the art of playing and recording, and we have a number of demos to show for our hard work.\n\nSince then, I''ve played with many different people, but focused mostly on a new project called Synergist with my fellow Torsion-ist drummer Chris Lyttle, and vocalist Craig McCutcheon. We''ve been playing around Toronto for a couple of years and recorded a number of songs for a planned full-length album we''re going to release independently. Hopefully this year!  It''s been a long road, but I''m sure we''ll have plenty of music to show for it. :)\n\nCheck out', 'MUSIC', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '245-autosave', '', '', '2013-03-25 03:25:11', '2013-03-25 03:25:11', '', 245, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=272', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
